<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-19878] Filtering on clustering columns in reversed order with BETWEEN return invalid results</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19878</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As noted by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=maedhroz&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;maedhroz&quot;&gt;maedhroz&lt;/a&gt;, filtering on clustering columns in reverser order do not work properly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem can be reproduced using the following test:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
@Test
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void testReverseAndBetweenMemtableFiltering()
{
    createTable(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;CREATE TABLE %s(p &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, c &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, c2 &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, abbreviation ascii, PRIMARY KEY (p, c, c2)) WITH CLUSTERING ORDER BY (c DESC, c2 DESC)&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);

    execute(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;INSERT INTO %s(p, c, c2, abbreviation) VALUES (0, 1, 1, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;CA&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
    execute(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;INSERT INTO %s(p, c, c2, abbreviation) VALUES (0, 2, 2, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;MA&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
    execute(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;INSERT INTO %s(p, c, c2, abbreviation) VALUES (0, 3, 3, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;MA&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
    execute(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;INSERT INTO %s(p, c, c2, abbreviation) VALUES (0, 4, 4, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;TX&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);

    ResultSet betweenRowsNet = executeNet(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;SELECT * FROM %s WHERE c2 BETWEEN 2 AND 3 ALLOW FILTERING&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
    assertRowsNet(betweenRowsNet, row (0, 3, 3, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;MA&quot;&lt;/span&gt;), row (0, 2, 2, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;MA&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)); &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// NO RESULTS?
&lt;/span&gt;}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue is due to the fact that the comparison performed in &lt;tt&gt;BETWEEN.isSatisfied&lt;/tt&gt; ignore the &lt;tt&gt;ReversedType&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
